l=https://wrsd.lima2019.pe/PAG2019/en/results/karate/athlete-profile-n1134316-kumizaki-valeria.htm|title=Val\u00e9ria Kumizaki|website=2019 Pan American Games|url-status=live|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> is a Brazilian [[karate]]ka. In 2019 she won the gold medal in the [[Karate at the 2019 Pan American Games|women's kumite -55 kg]] event at the [[2019 Pan American Games]] held in Lima, Peru.<ref name=\"karate_results_lima_2019\">{{Cite web|url=https://wrsd.lima2019.pe/PAG2019/resPAG2019/pdf/PAG2019/KTE/PAG2019_KTE_C93_KTE-------------------------------.pdf|title=Karate Results|website=2019 Pan American Games|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref> She also won the gold medal [[Karate at the 2015 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's 55 kg|in this event]] at the [[2015 Pan American Games]] held in Toronto, Canada.<ref name=\"warner_breaks_records_toronto_2015>{{Cite news|last=Pavitt|first=Michael|url=https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1028913/warner-breaks-pan-american-games-and-canadian-decathlon-records-to-claim-toronto-2015-gold|title=Warner breaks Pan American Games and Canadian decathlon records to claim Toronto 2015 gold|date=23 July 2015|work=InsideTheGames.biz|access-date=18 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In both events [[Kathryn Campbell (karateka)|Kathryn Campbell]] of Canada won the silver medal.<ref name=\"karate_results_lima_2019\"/><ref name=\"warner_breaks_records_toronto_2015/>\n\nAt the [[2017 World Games]] held in Wroc\u0142aw, Poland she won the gold medal in the women's kumite -55 kg event.<ref name=\"the_netherlands_ninth_title_world_games_2017\">{{Cite news|last=Winters|first=Max|url=https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1053246/the-netherlands-claim-ninth-world-games-korfball-title-in-a-row|title=The Netherlands claim ninth World Games korfball title in a row|date=25 July 2017|work=InsideTheGames.biz|access-date=18 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{sports lin